    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 16th is anchored by **Jackson Merrill**, who sits at the top of our lineup efficiency projections with a score of 67.37. Despite a challenging matchup against Luis Castillo, **Merrill** benefits significantly from his anticipated spot at the top of the order and a strong platoon advantage against the right-hander, making him a high-floor play. Following closely is **Jacob Wilson** (62.77), whose value is bolstered by a favorable park factor and a soft matchup against Leiter, providing a rare high-efficiency outlook for a middle-infield slot. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.04) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.95) occupy the core, they face moderate resistance from Sproat and Ashcraft respectively; however, their premium batting order positions provide enough volume to justify their spots.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup optimizer was balancing the marginal offensive potential of our bench against the risk-heavy profiles of our starters. **Brady House** (47.22) served as the closest cut, narrowly missing out due to a slight deficit in projected efficiency compared to **Josh Jung**, despite **House**\u2019s high stolen base upside against Ashcraft. Similarly, while **Nolan Schanuel** provided a solid floor, he was sidelined in favor of the higher-ceiling platoon splits offered by **Miguel Vargas**. We are closely monitoring a 44% rain risk in the game featuring **Gunnar Henderson**; if a delay or postponement seems imminent, we are prepared to pivot to a bench option to ensure we maximize our daily cap efficiency. **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s score is already depressed to 47.79 due to a tough lefty-on-lefty matchup, making him a prime candidate for a late swap if conditions deteriorate.",
